00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:15.330 align:middle line:10%
studying the unique
characteristics

00:01:15.330 --> 00:01:17.040 align:middle line:10%
of the male and female brains.

00:01:17.040 --> 00:01:19.270 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold,
we're totally different.

00:01:19.270 --> 00:01:22.480 align:middle line:84%
First off, the female brain
is wired for leadership.

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:25.200 align:middle line:84%
So why aren't we in more
positions of leadership?

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:27.690 align:middle line:84%
Kayla Osterhoff has
spent years researching

00:01:27.690 --> 00:01:29.790 align:middle line:84%
in this field of
gender neurobiology

00:01:29.790 --> 00:01:31.920 align:middle line:84%
and has come to some
profound discoveries.

00:01:31.920 --> 00:01:32.940 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Kayla.

00:01:32.940 --> 00:01:33.795 align:middle line:90%
We meet again.

00:01:33.795 --> 00:01:34.140 align:middle line:90%
>>OSTERHOFF: Yes.

00:01:34.140 --> 00:01:35.807 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm so happy
to have you here.

00:01:35.807 --> 00:01:39.420 align:middle line:84%
The last interview I did
with you got such a response

00:01:39.420 --> 00:01:41.760 align:middle line:84%
from women, because
they'd never heard this

